				},
				["TE"] = 1,
				["T1"] = {
					["TX"] = "{p:c}{col:535cff}  ___  _ _            ____           _ _         _\n / _ \\(_) || ___   _  ||  _ \\ ___ _ __(_) || ____ _|| ||_ ___\n|| || || || || ||/ / || || || || ||_) / _ \\ '__|| || ||/ / _` || __/ _ \\\n|| ||_|| || ||   <|| ||_|| || ||  __/  __/ ||  || ||   < (_|| || |||| (_) ||\n \\___/||_||_||\\_\\\\__,_|| ||_||   \\___||_||  ||_||_||\\_\\__,_||\\__\\___/{/col}{/p}\n\n\n\n{h1:c}{col:535cff}Oiku Perikato{/col}{/h1}\n{h2:c}{col:9dafff}Troubleshooter of the Perikato Caravan{/col}{/h2}\n\n{p:c}{col:9f9f9f}Oiku seems quite chipper for someone his age, and quite evidently so through his pure eyes and smooth fluff. He is after all, young enough to be able to perceive the strong colors of the world, as if there was never a care for him in the world...{/col}{/p}\n\n{p:c}{col:9f9f9f}...Atleast that would have been the case, had it not been for the camp incident.{/col}{/p}\n\n{p:c}{col:9f9f9f}Oiku's seemingly struggling feature, is the inability to trust others. While he has much of a passion for his voice to be heard from his obsession of technology, wishing to help others, he finds an insane amount of trouble attempting to keep up a conversation. It is as if those rights were taken from him, as if he has been under a year's worth of shock. He could never explain the feelings enveloping within him after that moment. He remembers 'everything' about the incident, and probably will continue to remember, as a traumatic symbol for a tainted future.{/p}\n\n\n{p:c}{col:535cff} ____  _           _        __        ___     _\n||  _ \\(_)_ __ __ _|| ||_ ___  \\ \\      / / ||__ (_)____\n|| ||_) || || '__/ _` || __/ _ \\  \\ \\ /\\ / /|| '_ \\|| ||_  /\n||  __/|| || || || (_|| || ||||  __/   \\ V  V / || || || || ||/ /\n||_||   ||_||_||  \\__,_||\\__\\___||    \\_/\\_/  ||_|| ||_||_/___||\n{/col}{/p}\n\n{h1:c}{col:535cff}Pirate Whiz{/col}{/h1}\n\n{p:c}{col:9f9f9f}Oiku didn't consider himself much of a pirate lackey, although the idea of being one filled him with enthusiasm. Sometime during his ventures in Vol'dun, he took an expedited visit to Freehold to aid locals in upgrading their technology to assist them with everyday life. Although he was not able to do so abundantly, due to his limitations of resource, he has been on the hunt for locked vaults hidden within the dunes that contain material that is essential for his building of technical electronic components. It would be unwise to ask him about silicon, for he will most likely enthusiastically explain it until the sun sets.{/col}{/p}\n\n",
